# Build-context excludes (context is the repo root; see docker-compose.yml).
#
# CRITICAL: never let host-built artifacts leak into images. The Dockerfiles
# COPY `packages` and `apps/<app>` and then run `pnpm install` inside the image.
# If the host's `.next` Turbopack cache or host `node_modules` symlinks are
# copied in, the dev server reads cache entries that reference host paths and
# panics with "Next.js package not found" (an intermittent crash-loop that
# manifests as an endless browser refresh). Excluding them forces a clean,
# deterministic install from source. Built package `dist/` is intentionally
# NOT excluded — core/auth/notesync-schema resolve via dist (built per the
# CLAUDE.md build order before `docker compose build`).
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# VCS / tooling / local junk
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log

# Test + report output
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/.playwright
